INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES(79, '52nd ANNUAL MEETING OF THE INTERNATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF JUDGES ', '52nd-annual-meeting-of-the-international-association-of-judges-', '', '<p><font color="#993366">52<sup>nd</sup> ANNUAL MEETING OF THE INTERNATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF JUDGES </font></p><p><font color="#993366">Marrakech (Morocco), 11th - 15th October 2009</font></p><p>         March 10th, 2009</p>', '<p>TO ALL NATIONAL MEMBER-ASSOCIATIONS</p><p>Dear Colleagues,</p><p>1 - In the name of the International Association of Judges and of the Amicale Hassania des magistrats du Maroc, I take pleasure in inviting you to name your delegates to the meetings of the Central Council and of the four Study Commissions of the IAJ to be held in Marrakech (Morocco) from 11th to 15th October 2009.</p><p>2 - The meetings will take place at the Hotel Mansour Eddahbi – Palais des Congrès in Marrakech.<br />The accommodation expenses must be covered by each national association for its own delegates.<br /> The Amicale Hassania des Magistrats will offer at its own expenses the simultaneous translation (English, French, Spanish), meeting rooms, a welcome party on Sunday October 11th, an excursion to Casablanca on Tuesday October 13th, a music concert and the farewell party on Wednesday October 14th plus other possible events.<br />The participation fee for accompanying persons amounts to 3.000 Dirhams.</p><p>3 - The delegates are expected to arrive on Sunday 11th October 2009 and are expected to leave on Thursday 15th October in the afternoon.<br />Transport service is available from Menara Marrakech airport to the hotel and from the hotel to the airport, at the price of 200 Dirhams (round-trip).</p><p>4 - Please find here enclosed a provisional programme. A special programme will be arranged for travelling companions. </p><p>5 - A special free excursion to Casablanca is scheduled on Tuesday 13th October for the participants and the accompanying persons. Other tourist programmes related to the city of Marrakech and its region may be requested and booked directly by the participants and their accompanying persons at the travel agency “Blue Events”, which will offer favourable prices and whose address is the following: 193, Boulevard Hassan II, 193, 5e étage, Casablanca ; tél. : +212 522 29 90 91 ; fax : +212 522 27 01 98 ; e-mail : <a href="mailto:congresuim52@gmail.com">congresuim52@gmail.com</a></p><p>6 - A certain number of rooms has been reserved at the hotel Mansour Eddahbi – Palais des Congrès, where the delegates will be hosted at their own expenses. The following costs of the accommodation have been communicated by the organising association:<br />single room: 1.200 Dirhams / Night<br />double room: 1.550 Dirhams / Night<br />Prices will be calculated at the exchange rate of the day of payment. So the prices in this letter are presented in MAD (Moroccan dirham) and the value in Euro has only indicative purposes (for your information, today''s official exchange rate is 1 MAD = 0,090 Euro).<br /> <br />7 - According to the criteria already adopted for previous meetings, delegates can be appointed as follows:<br />- each association belonging to the 1st group is entitled to send a maximum of 6 delegates;<br />- each association belonging to the 2nd group is entitled to send a maximum of 5 delegates;<br />- each association belonging to the 3rd group is entitled to send a maximum of 4 delegates;<br />- each association belonging to the 4th group is entitled to send a maximum of 3 delegates;<br />- each extraordinary member is entitled to send a maximum of 2 delegates.</p><p>8 - Since the organisation has to confirm the reservation of the rooms on time, the national associations are urged to forward immediately to the members of their delegations two copies of the enclosed registration forms, asking them to fill in the forms and to send one to each of the following addresses to arrive before May 15th, 2009:</p><p>to:        and to:<br />Mr Mohamed SEDKI D.G.<br />Ms. Amira ELALMI Chargée de Projet.</p><p>Blue Events S.A.R.L.<br />193, Boulevard Hassan II, 5e étage, Casablanca<br />Bureau : +212 522 29 90 91<br />Fax : +212 522 27 01 98</p><p>e-mail : <a href="mailto:congresuim52@gmail.com">congresuim52@gmail.com</a> Mr. Antonio Mura<br />Secretary-General of the IAJ</p><p>Palazzo di Giustizia <br />Piazza Cavour - 00193 Roma, Italy</p><p>Tel.: +39 06 6883 2213<br />Fax: +39 06 687 11 95<br />E-mail: <a href="mailto:secretariat@iaj-uim.org">secretariat@iaj-uim.org</a> </p><p> 9 - Each national association is kindly requested to send the list of its delegates (to the Central Council and to the Study Commissions) both to Mr. Antonio Mura and Mr. Mostafa Fares, Procureur Général du Roi, Cour d''appel du commerce, Casablanca , Morocco; tel.: +212 661 30 19 33; br : +212 522 37 98 75; fax: +212 522 47 41 10; email: <a href="mailto:h1amical@yahoo.fr">h1amical@yahoo.fr</a>. <br />Any modifications to the list should be communicated in the same way, and each communication should mention that a copy has been sent to Marrakech or to Rome. Any communication concerning logistics and hotel reservations should be sent only to Mr. Mostafa Fares.</p><p>10 - Delegates are kindly requested to respect the time-limit fixed (May 15th, 2009), risking otherwise to be unable to take part in the meeting.</p><p>11 - The climate in Marrakech is expected to be pleasant and the temperature in the range of approx. 20 to 25 degrees Celsius (68/77 degrees Fahrenheit).</p><p> Looking forward to seeing you in Marrakech, I send you all my best wishes.</p><p>   Yours sincerely,</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Antonio Mura<br />Secretary-General<br />   International Association of Judges</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>P.S. <br />- In addition to the meetings of the Central Council and of the Study Commissions, the following meetings will take place in Yerevan:<br />a) a meeting of the Presidency Committee on Saturday, October 10th, in the afternoon;<br />b) meetings of the European Association of Judges - Regional Group of the IAJ, of the Ibero-American Regional Group, of the African Regional Group and of the Asian, Oceanian and North American Regional Group, on Sunday, October 11th.</p><p>- One delegate from each association should arrive on Saturday October 10th evening, to participate in the Sunday morning Regional Groups’ meetings. </p><p>- The following subjects will be discussed by the Study-Commissions in Yerevan: <br />“Ways to identify and classify criteria, objective and subjective, by reference to which the independence of the judiciary may be assessed” (1st Study Commission); <br />“The treatment of commercial disputes” (2nd Study Commission); <br />“Interception of communications and its impact on privacy rights” (3rd Study Commission); <br />“Equal opportunity in employment for disabled and older persons” (4th Study Commission).</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Here enclosed please find:<br />a) the provisional programme;<br />b) the registration form for the meeting.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><br />PROVISIONAL PROGRAMME<br />for the <br />52nd Annual Meeting of the IAJ<br />MARRAKEC (MOROCCO), 11th - 15th October 2009</p><p><br />Saturday, 10th October 2009<br />15.00 - 18.00 Meeting of the Presidency Committee<br />Sunday, 11th October 2009<br />10.00 - 17.00 Meeting of the European Association of Judges<br />10.00 - 17.00 Meeting of the Ibero-American Regional Group<br />10.00 - 17.00 Meeting of the African Regional Group<br />10.00 - 17.00 Meeting of the Asian, North American and Oceanian Regional Group<br />11.30 - 12.00 Coffee-break<br />13.15 - 14.45 Lunch<br />16.00 - 16.30 Coffee-break<br />17.00 - 19.00 Meeting of the Presidency Committee<br />20.00 - Welcome party <br />Monday, 12th October 2009<br />09.30 - 12.00 Opening Ceremony: speeches of the President of the Amicale Hassania des Magistrats, of the Ministry of Justice, of the Chairman of the Supreme Court, of the General Attorney of the Supreme Court, of the President of the IAJ<br />12.00 - 14.00 Official Lunch <br />14.00 - 16.00 Meeting of the Central Council (1st part)<br />16.00 - 16.15 Coffee break<br />16.15 - 19.00 Meetings of the Study Commissions (1st part)<br />19.00 - 20.30 Piano Concert <br />21.00 - Dinner<br />Tuesday, 13th October 2009<br />08.00 till evening Excursion to Casablanca<br />Evening Dinner <br />Wednesday, 14th October 2009<br />09.30 - 13.00 Meetings of the Study Commissions (2nd part)<br />13.15 - 14.45 Lunch<br />15.00 - 15.30 Photo-session<br />15.30 - 18.00 Meeting of the Central Council (2nd part)<br />20.00 Farewell Dinner<br />Thursday, 15th October 2009<br />10.00 - 12.00 Meeting of the Central Council (3rd part)<br />From 13.00 Departure of the delegates</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 1, 0, 35, '2009-03-11 13:39:03', 64, '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2009-03-11 13:39:03', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 1, 0, 175, '', '', 0, 10008, 'robots=\nauthor=');
